// bisect: GIR/emit bug (interp != fused)
// interp/jit: Before the fix, `graphix-fuzz run` reported Interp=Timeout (canonical node-walk), Fused=Value(i64:2) (WRONG), Jit=Timeout. After the fix all three are Timeout (bottom).
// root_cause: A bottom (None) scrutinee must poison the whole select — the node-walk's Select node only fires when the scrutinee has a value. The fused IfChain/Select folded the scrutinee into the per-arm conditions (`scrut == literal`), so a bottom scrutinee made the first conditional arm's cond bottom (skipped), and the unconditional catch-all (`_ => 2`, cond None) then matched → it returned 2 instead of bottom. Fix: GirOp::IfChain / GirStmt::Select gained a `scrut` field, lowered from emit_select{,_as_expr}; gir_interp evaluates it ONCE up front and a bottom scrutinee returns None (poison) before any arm is tried. Distinct from a bottom arm GUARD, which only makes that arm fail to match (unchanged).
{ let v = i64:1 / i64:0; select v { 0 => i64:1, _ => i64:2 } }
